Flash floods in KwaZulu-Natal has left one person dead. Severe rain fell in the Nonoti and Kwadakuza areas overnight and three vehicles were swept off a low lying bridge. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Flash floods in KwaZulu-Natal has left one person dead. Severe rain fell in the Nonoti and Kwadakuza areas overnight and three vehicles were swept off a low lying bridge. READ: Flood warning issued for parts of SA Three people managed to escape to higher ground. But a 28-year-old woman lost her footing and got caught in the strong floodwaters. She was located by rescue services.